    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl>Morelli in <ptr target="#SECir"/>, <citedRange>215</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>102810</citedRange></bibl>. 
                    Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#parisipresicce2007a"/><citedRange/></bibl> and 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#luni2014b"/>, pp. <citedRange>129, 133</citedRange></bibl> (circumstances of find).</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                            <ab>
                                <lb n="1"/><milestone unit="block" n="a"/><persName type="divine" ref="#Apollo"><name nymRef="#Ἀπόλλων">Ἀπόλλōν<unclear>ος</unclear></name></persName> 
                                <gap reason="lost" quantity="8" precision="low" unit="character"/> 
                                <milestone unit="block" n="b"/><persName type="divine" ref="#Aphrodite"><name nymRef="#Ἀφροδίτα">Ἀφροδίτας</name></persName> 
                                <space quantity="2" unit="character"/> 
                                <persName type="divine" ref="#Hekate"><name nymRef="#Ἑκάτα">Ἑκάτας</name></persName>    
                            </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                 <p>
                     <app loc="1">
                         <lem>Ἀπόλλōν<unclear>ος</unclear> <gap reason="lost" quantity="8" precision="low" unit="character"/></lem>
                     <rdg resp="#SECir"><note>block a was not mentioned nor transcribed by Morelli</note></rdg></app></p>
               </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Autels d'</supplied> Apollon, de <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>, d'Aphrodite, d'Hécate.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Altars of </supplied> Apollo, of <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>, of Aphrodite, of Hekate.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Altari di </supplied> Apollo, di <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>, di Afrodite, di Ecate.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>The photograph in <bibl><ptr target="#SECir"/>, <citedRange>215</citedRange>, fig. 159</bibl> clearly shows two similar and adjoining blocks and allows to read at least the first name 
                    inscribed on block a.</p>
                <p/>
            </div></body>
